Ngeneric:Invisible-Pin|pin@53||-74|22|||||SIM_spice_card(D5G1;)S[* CMOS Inverter Simulation for Electric VLSI Schematic,* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* 1. Model Definitions,* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* Using generic Level 1 models for simulation purposes.,"* In a real fabrication process, you would include a specific .lib file here.",.model N_Model nmos level=1,.model P_Model pmos level=1,* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* 2. Circuit Netlist (Component Connections),* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* Syntax: M<name> <drain> <gate> <source> <body > <model> W=<width> L=<length>,* PMOS Transistor (Top),"* Source connected to VDD, Drain to Output (B), Gate to Input (A), Body to VDD",M1 B A vdd vdd P_Model W=4u L=2u,* NMOS Transistor (Bottom),"* Source connected to GND (0), Drain to Output (B), Gate to Input (A), Body to GND (0)",M2 B A 0 0 N_Model W=2u L=2u,* Note: I used W=4u for PMOS and W=2u for NMOS (2:1 ratio) to balance ,"* rise/fall times, which is standard practice, though the image shows \"2\" for both.",* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* 3. Power Supplies and Input Sources,* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* VDD Supply Voltage (5V) connected between node 'vdd' and Ground '0',Vsupply vdd 0 DC 5,* Input Pulse Source (Applied to node A),* PULSE(V_low V_high delay rise_time fall_time pulse_width period),Vin A 0 PULSE(0 5 1n 1n 1n 10n 20n),* ------------------------------------------------------------------,* 4. Simulation Control Block,* ------------------------------------------------------------------,.control,"    * Perform a Transient Analysis: step=0.1ns, stop=50ns",    tran 0.1n 50n,    * Plot Input (A) and Output (B) voltages,    plot v(A) v(B),.endc,.end]
